2026-04-12: TP: 70% unit, 20% integration, 10% e2e
  - Unit tests (Jest) catch logic instantly (< 100ms suite); integration tests verify service boundaries; e2e (Playwright) for critical workflows only
  - Coverage targets: 80% backend controllers, 85% business logic, 70% database queries, 60% components, 50% integration flows
  - Factory functions generate realistic fixtures; isolated database per test via transaction rollback (200ms teardown)
  - Flaky test detection: 5x runs flag problematic tests; slow tests (>5s) parallelized maintaining < 5min total CI runtime
  - Test names describe behavior ("should prevent duplicate titles"); arrange-act-assert structure; mocking external services
